    <briefdescription>
<para>A set of functions for selecting segments on a mesh. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<sect1 id="group__MeshSegmentationGroup_1MeshSegmentationGroup_HowTo">
<title>How To</title><para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Make Contour(-s)<linebreak/>
First step to get a mesh segment by two (/three) points, is getting the contour that bounds the segment.<linebreak/>
To do this, you can use <ref refid="group__MeshSegmentationGroup_1ga92dbf357e425dd6e8d7f76ab544250c5" kindref="member">surroundingContour</ref></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Get Segment<linebreak/>
For getting segment of mesh by contour(-s) use <ref refid="group__MeshSegmentationGroup_1gadea0ef926186e71514bcaf05a50aa51d" kindref="member">fillContourLeftByGraphCut</ref>.</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
